9.15.24  9:06 pm   why do we even consider male and female opposites? are they?

      they are counterparts, in the process of biological reproduction. for typical biological reproduction in our species (and others) you need 1 of each. but of course they are extremely similar to each other because of being the same species. in that sense, most things that are considered 'opposites' are almost identical. such as a left shoe and a right shoe
